Title: Simplicial Chiral Models
Authors: Paolo Rossi (INFN at Pisa) and Chung-I Tan (Brown Univ.)
Comments: 6 pages, PHYZZX
Report-no: BROWN-HET-974, IFUP-TH75/94
Journal-ref: Phys.Rev. D51 (1995) 7159-7161
\\
  Principal chiral models on a d-1 dimensional simplex are introduced and
studied analytically in the large $N$ limit. The $d = 0, 2, 4$ and $\infty$
models are explicitly solved. Relationship with standard lattice models and
with few-matrix systems in the double scaling limit are discussed.
